description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join our progressive Pharmacy team as a Rotational Pharmacy Technician working across the Pharmacy and ward areas to grow and drive our Medicines Optimisation services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is integral to delivering our Medicines Optimisation vision and, as such, we are looking for an applicant with real passion for the profession and the drive to develop.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will play a pivotal role in shaping the pharmacy services throughout the Trust and should be adaptable to new situations and be confident to work independently and as part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We place a high importance on career development and continuing education opportunities and are keen to meet technicians with a similar desire to progress.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information or an informal visit please contact Emily Wardle, Chief Pharmacy Technician on 01423 557728, or email emily.wardle@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**This job advert will close as soon as a sufficient amount of applications have been received. Please apply for this job as soon as you can, if you are interested.**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
